    <p><img style="float: right;" src="http://www.ostraining.com/images/drupal/contextual-filter.png" alt="contextual-filter" />Sometimes the name you give something is really important.&nbsp;</p>
<p>In Drupal 6, a key feature in Views was called "arguments". This term made perfect sense to developers, but caused plenty of raised eyebrows amongst news users.</p>
<p>Both the name and location of this feature has changed in Drupal 7. Arguments are now called "Contextual filters".</p>
<p>Here's an introduction to arguments and contextual filters. We'll show you why they are so useful, whatever they may be called.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ostrainingdrupal/~4/U8yDQZc4Cww" height="1" width="1"/>
